The paper discusses a personalized recommendation model using collaborative tags, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SOC). The use of diffusion-based process for calculating user similarity is a technique commonly used in machine learning and deep learning (cs.DL), and the integration of two kinds of similarities is a form of ensemble learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses metrics such as ranking score, Recall and Precision, which are commonly used in information retrieval and machine learning evaluation (cs.SI).
